<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-79-0679 </DOCNO><TEXT>Wind power generation in California, USA is active with its share of 90%in the world (1985). The size of the wind power generation units practicallyused in USA and Denmark is less than several hundred kW. Mitsubishi HeavyIndustries of Japan exported in 1987 sixty units of wind power generatorto California and Hawaii. The world-wide trend in the wind power generationis the development of a larger size exceeding 1 MW. However, the largesize wind-mill involves a lot of difficulty, and will require considerabletime. This booklet describes the following items. Wind energy. Historyof wind-mill. Features of wind power generation. Mechanism of wind powergeneration. Development in Japan. Development overseas. Influence toenvironment. Economy of wind power generation. In Japan, the suitableland is found only in Hokkaido. (18 figs, 9 tabs, 8 refs)</TEXT></DOC>